24/03/2011
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Macedonian Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski and Greek counterpart George Papandreou will meet on Thursday (March 24th) in Brussels on the side lines of the European Council. They are expected to discuss bilateral issues and regional topics. Gruevski will also hold talks with EU foreign policy chief Catherine Ashton and Enlargement Commissioner Stefan Fuele. (MIA, Kanal 5, Alsat M - 23/03/11)
